t</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":85,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":94,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert De Blanchville was born about 1130, in England. She had at least 1 son with Robert De Blanchville."},"et":{"about 1130–":"umbes 1130–Surnud","1145–1201":"1145–1201","–1225":"–1225","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1145":"1145","1130":"1130","about 1130":"umbes 1130","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1130–":"noin 1130–Kuollut","1145–1201":"1145–1201","–1225":"–1225","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1145":"1145","1130":"1130","about 1130":"noin 1130","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1130–":